(Overview) Tj
T*
(Letter writing teaches purpose, format, tone, and audience awareness.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Learning Objectives) Tj
T*
(- Explain the meaning of Letter Writing in English using accurate subject vocabulary.) Tj
T*
(- Describe the key ideas behind formal and informal structures and suitable language.) Tj
T*
(- Apply Letter Writing to examples such as writing a formal request letter with proper) Tj
T*
(layout.) Tj
T*
(- Avoid common errors and build confidence through formal and informal letter tasks.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Main Lesson) Tj
T*
(1. Introduction To The Topic) Tj
T*
(Letter writing teaches purpose, format, tone, and audience awareness. In a textbook) Tj
T*
(lesson, the first goal is to make the language idea clear. Students should be able to) Tj
T*
(explain what Letter Writing means, identify where it appears in English, and describe) Tj
T*
(the main purpose of the topic without relying on memorized sentences.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Core Teaching) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Letter Writing is formal and informal structures and suitable) Tj
T*
(language. This means students must move beyond the overview and understand how the idea) Tj
T*
(actually works. A strong explanation should unpack the rules, relationships, or patterns) Tj
T*
(behind Letter Writing and show how those ideas guide correct answers. In English,) Tj
T*
(success usually depends on understanding the meaning, form, and effect that belong to) Tj
T*
(the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. How The Idea Is Applied) Tj
T*
(A useful way to teach Letter Writing is to connect the explanation directly to writing a) Tj
T*
(formal request letter with proper layout. That kind of language example shows students) Tj
T*
(how the topic moves from theory into use. At this stage, the learner should be able to) Tj
T*
(state the relevant rule or principle, explain why it fits the question, and then apply) Tj
T*
(the interpretation or writing method with confidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Why Errors Happen) Tj
T*
(One common difficulty in Letter Writing is mixing formal tone with casual expressions.) Tj
T*
(This matters because many learners can repeat a definition but still fail to use it) Tj
T*
(correctly. A real textbook lesson should therefore point out not only the correct) Tj
T*
